title: A history of the voyages and travels of Capt. Nathaniel Uring. With new draughts of the Bay of Honduras and the Caribbee Islands; and particularly of St. Lucia, and the harbour of Petite Carenage; into which ships may run in bad weather, and be safe from all winds and storms. Very useful for masters of ships that use the Leeward Island trade, or Jamaica.
